indicator.description:
(1) Number of biodiversity based products developed by pilot community-based social enterprises certified sustainable;
(2) Availability of biodiversity-based promotional mark to support products from community-based social enterprises;
(3) Percentage of land and sea-scape managed by target communities is under sustainable management.;
(4) Extent to which institutional and staff capacity of Biodiversity-based Economy Development (BEDO) strengthened.

actual.comment:
4 Pilot REOs and the national project management unit have accumulated more hands-on capacities building as part of the process in developing the PES scheme in each locality. 

Key capacities strengthened through the learning by doing process included: 

(1)	Bio-carbon assessment and monitoring; 

(2)	Survey and monitoring process for key indicator species;

(3)	Engagement with communities in developing the community PES action plans as well as capacity buildings for communities to conduct local monitoring of bio-carbon and biodiversity resources in the areas;  

(4)	Economic valuation for the key ecosystem services in the pilot areas, as part of the consultant’s works on economic valuation started in April – October 2015.

At midterm point of the project, it can be said that the 4 pilot REOs have acquired theoretical understanding as well as hands-on experiences in developing PES schemes, even though the degree of understanding varies from one REO to the other. The pilot REOs as well as the project management unit have also been more exposed to exchanges of experiences with other projects in the country, notably the GIZ-supported ECO-BEST, aiming at operationalising TEEB and the USAID-LEAF, aiming at exploring the Low Emission Actions in the Forest Sector; and outside the country.  The Project Manager attended   The Regional Workshop on Payment for Environment Services held from 24-25 November 2014, in Hanoi City, Vietnam in order to exchange of experience on the application of PES schemes and foster collaboration and partnership among stakeholder in the Greater Mekong Region.

